@node Program "About the Program"

@{u}About the Program@{uu}

Adcom was written in about a hour after I got tired of wondering what
all those .lha files in my downloads directory are.

You see what I generally do is logon to Aminet get the RECENT file and 
download all the files I think may be of interest.

The problem arises when I later look in my downloads directory and
there are loads of .lha files.

I decided to write a little AREXX program to search a directory
for the RECENT file.  It then looks at each of the files in the same
directory and any filenames that exist in the RECENT file it attaches
the short comment from the RECENT file.

Got that?

Now I can see at a glance what they are just by looking at the filenote.

@endnode
